subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Males are distinguished by the configuration of the bulbus, notably the complex shape of the apical part of the conductor (
Fig. 109
); females by the configuration of the epigyne (
Fig. 111
).

Prosoma. Carapace (
Fig. 4
) sooty brown with lighter median band and lateral bands broken into lighter patches. Thoracic part with recumbent dark pubescence (light hairs seem to have gone in the specimens at hand). Clypeus yellowish. Chelicerae brownish with sooty streaks, inner side lighter, retromargin with 3 teeth (in lectotype the inner and middle one nearly fused). Sternum brownish grey to blackish.

Opisthosoma. Dorsum (
Fig. 4
) more or less sooty brown, with lighter brown lanceolate stripe followed by a series of transversally arranged light patches, posterior confluent to bars, each patch with a black dot. Venter light to greyish brown with light recumbent pubescence.

Legs (
Table 1
). Yellow with sooty pseudoannulation dorsally on all femora (Fe I with confluent sooty patch dorsally in proximal half). Hairiness in leg I similar to that of the other legs. Ti I retrolaterally with two spines or only one in proximal half.

Legs (
Table 1
). Yellowish-brown. Femora with darker pseudoannulation. Ti retrolaterally with one spine in proximal half.

Distribution (
Fig. 116
). China ( Inner Mongolia , Beijing , Hebei , Shanxi , Gansu , Qinghai (
Song et al. 2001
)). Because of previous confusion with P. z y u z i n i sp. nov. some records need to be verified.
